span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;icle/2/10/pgad293/7330949&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fediscience.org/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111330330783507463</guid><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 15:27:12 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>James Gleick</title><link>https://zirk.us/@JamesGleick/111330236680022462</link><description>Here is the first act of the new right-wing Republican leadership of the House: As a condition of aiding Israel, they insist on defunding the IRS’s ability to go after rich tax cheats.Not sure why that isn’t getting bigger play in the mainstream press.&lt;a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2023/10/31/israel-ukraine-congress-senate-austin-blinken/a47a753e-77a2-11ee-97dd-7a173b1bd730_story.html" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;washingtonpost.com/politics/20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;23/10/31/israel-ukraine-congress-senate-austin-blinken/a47a753e-77a2-11ee-97dd-7a173b1bd730_story.html&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111331141305219770</guid><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 18:53:21 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Lucas Cantor</title><link>https://infosec.exchange/@lucas/111330446537569098</link><description>Your annual reminder that Halloween is by far the deadliest day of the year for children in the US.It's not due to poison in the candy, stranger danger, or spooky satanists, though...It's cars. Kids are routinely hit and killed by cars, and we don't bat an eye, let alone change anything. This is what real horror looks like.Children are three times more likely to be fatally injured by a car on Halloween, and the risk grows to 10 times for kids aged 4 to 8.&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://infosec.exchange/tags/BikeTooter" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;BikeTooter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://infosec.exchange/tags/CarFree" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;CarFree&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://infosec.exchange/tags/Halloween" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Halloween&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://infosec.exchange/tags/KidicalMass" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;KidicalMass&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/330/446/563/547/010/original/9f09d13b59d34c24.jpeg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/330/446/563/547/010/original/9f09d13b59d34c24.jpeg" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111331146716459915</guid><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 18:54:43 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Prof Stephen Serjeant</title><link>https://mas.to/@stephenserjeant/111331002444733626</link><description>&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mas.to/tags/UKRI" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;UKRI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; have caved. Most alarming of all in the response is UKRI's review of advisory body appointments. &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mas.to/tags/DfE" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;DfE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; already monitor social media of teachers critical of govt policy, &amp;amp; govt has blocked govt-critical scientists from speaking in their expert capacities at govt events &lt;a href="https://www.ukri.org/news/response-to-the-open-letter-from-the-secretary-of-state/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;ukri.org/news/response-to-the-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;open-letter-from-the-secretary-of-state/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111331153058461760</guid><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 18:56:20 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/111331206859159822</link><description>Early selection of task-relevant features through population gating&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-023-42519-5" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;nature.com/articles/s41467-023&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;-42519-5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fediscience.org/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111331206968060504</guid><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 19:10:01 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/111331212142101773</link><description>Numerical Representation for Action in Crows Obeys the Weber-Fechner Law&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/10.1177/09567976231201624" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;10.1177/09567976231201624&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111331212231516569</guid><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 19:11:22 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/111331225620075708</link><description>"The neural code has three syllables: silences, spikes, and bursts"Silences, spikes and bursts: Three-part knot of the neural code&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://physoc.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1113/JP281510" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;physoc.onlinelibrary.wiley.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;/doi/full/10.1113/JP281510&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fediscience.org/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111331225752459025</guid><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 19:14:47 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/111331240226829784</link><description>Beta as a top-down mechanism.Phasic modulation of beta power at movement related frequencies during visuomotor conflict&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://journals.physiology.org/doi/abs/10.1152/jn.00338.2023" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;journals.physiology.org/doi/ab&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;s/10.1152/jn.00338.2023&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fediscience.org/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111331240291622091</guid><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 19:18:30 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Carl Zimmer</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@Carl_Zimmer/111331659791553334</link><description>Over five thousand sea lions killed in Peru by bird flu. &lt;a href="https://wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/article/29/12/23-0192_article" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/article/29/1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;2/23-0192_article&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111331659791553334</guid><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 21:05:12 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>BrainGlobe</title><link>https://mastodon.online/@brainglobe/111330496432789009</link><description>Hi everyone! The BrainGlobe Initiative exists to facilitate the development of interoperable Python-based tools for computational neuroanatomy, particularly in model organisms.For more details please see &lt;a href="https://brainglobe.info" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;brainglobe.info&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; or chat with us at &lt;a href="https://brainglobe.zulipchat.com" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;brainglobe.zulipchat.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.online/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111331672067430041</guid><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 21:08:20 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Steven Strogatz</title><link>https://mathstodon.xyz/@stevenstrogatz/111331771980642748</link><description>I just posted two video lectures from my undergrad complex analysis course. One is about Cauchy's theorem and the other is  about Jordan's lemma. They both involve beautiful mathematical arguments – I hope you enjoy them! Cauchy’s theorem&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://youtu.be/AjrkNlgwT_U" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;youtu.be/AjrkNlgwT_U&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Jordan’s lemma&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://youtu.be/C5rukxDDW8U" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;youtu.be/C5rukxDDW8U&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Someday I hope to post all the lectures in this course, but for now I'm just posting occasional Zoom videos that I've recorded for whatever random reason.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111331772119799353</guid><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 21:33:44 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Laffy</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@GottaLaff/111329828991508091</link><description>1/... Senate Judiciary Committee  announced plans to vote to subpoena billionaires who reportedly gave lavish gifts to &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/SupremeCourt" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;SupremeCourt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Justices &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/ClarenceThomas" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;ClarenceThomas&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &amp;amp; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/Alito" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Alito&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.Sen. Durbin (D-Ill.) &amp;amp; Sen. Whitehouse (D-R.I.) said in a statement that they plan to subpoena billionaires Harlan Crow &amp;amp; Robin Arkley, as well as conservative judicial activist Leonard Leo. &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/SCOTUS" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;SCOTUS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.axios.com/2023/10/31/democrats-supoena-harlan-crow-leonard-leo-supreme-court-justices" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;axios.com/2023/10/31/democrats&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;-supoena-harlan-crow-leonard-leo-supreme-court-justices&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="fal